<div class="subtitle">Concept</div>
<P>
The user interface of MMM consists of a <a href="main_window.html">main window</a> for primary control, a <a href="model_window.html">model window</a> for high-resolution display and fine control of the 3D view, a <a href="hierarchy_window.html">hierarchy window</a> for a convenient overview of structures and selection of objects (structures, chains, residues and cofactors, atoms, atom locations) and several auxiliary windows for special tasks, such as influencing model visualization (<a href="color_selection.html">coloring</a>, <a href="transparency_selection.html">changing object transparency</a>, <a href="graphics_selection.html">graphics mode</a>), <a href="annotation_window.html">annotation</a>, and managing <a href="reference_window.html">references</a>
</p>
